sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS change_count
FROM annotation_changes
WHERE changed_by = 1;

SELECT release_date
FROM annotation_releases
WHERE status = 'archived';

external_knowledge:
This query assumes that the most recent modification is the one with the latest date; 
The chromosome number is an identifier for the chromosome to which the annotation belongs; 
The annotation is a piece of information about a specific location in the genome assembly.

sql:
SELECT MAX(release_date)
FROM annotation_versions
WHERE annotation_id = 1;

SELECT assembly_name
FROM assemblies
WHERE assembly_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_release_count
FROM annotation_releases
WHERE status = 'current';
